    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-06-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-06-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="683"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d683">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 25010/24.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Italian Chargé</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Italian Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Manchester, Mass.</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-06-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 27, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Urgent. Judge Blair insists on having preliminary mandate prescribed in article 2
                    of convention of 1884, so as to maintain arrest of Porter Charlton. I beg you,
                    your excellency, to urgently send me or directly to Italian consul. New York,
                    the said document, so that arrest of murderer be maintained until a decision can
                    be taken on the question.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Montagliari.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
